    "long_instructions": "Add additional beat, bass, and lead tracks to the vocals in this track. Each new track should start 1 measure after the last, creating a \"build\" effect. Listen to the example song for one possible way to solve this.\r\n\r\nYou will need to use `play together`, `play sequential`, and `rest` blocks strategically to achieve this effect.\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>Mini-rubric Details</summary>\r\n  <table>\r\n  <tr style=\"border: 1px solid black; padding: 1px\">\r\n\t  <td>Extensive Evidence</td>\r\n\t  <td>critera</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr style=\"border: 1px solid black; padding: 1px\">\r\n\t  <td>Convincing Evidence</td>\r\n\t  <td>critera</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr style=\"border: 1px solid black; padding: 1px\">\r\n\t  <td>Limited Evidence</td>\r\n\t  <td>critera</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr style=\"border: 1px solid black; padding: 1px\">\r\n\t  <td>No Evidence</td>\r\n\t  <td>critera</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  </table>\r\n</details>",
